text: Renan Barbosa Contar (born December 25, 1983) is a Brazilian politician, currently a state deputy for Mato Grosso do Sul. He is currently running in the second round for the government of Mato Grosso do Sul. He attended the Preparatory School of Cadets for the Army in 2002 in Campinas, Brazil.
